&lt;p&gt;Community Learning Disability Nurse/Complex Needs Practitioner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity has arisen for a registered Learning Disability, Mental Health or Child Nurse to work as part of a multi-disciplinary team within the Preston Childrens Learning Disability / Complex Needs Service. To take a lead role in the delivery of high quality service provision that promotes and improves the well-being of children and young people who have a learning disability or are on the Autism Spectrum. Working within a systemic and holistic framework you will undertake needs led, evidence based, assessments and therapeutic interventions with children and young people, their families and carers, who present to the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Children’s Learning Disability / Complex Needs Service is part of Lancashire &amp; South Cumbria NHS Foundation Trust, Learning Disability Service. The service is committed to providing a high quality, effective service to the population of Central Lancashire. The Service provides a variety of client based assessments and interventions, training and education, strategic group and community level work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will, as part of a multi-disciplinary team, work towards addressing the health, psychological, emotional and behavioural needs of children and young people with a learning disability and/or autism. They will be responsible for their caseload and supervise that of other practitioners within the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is based within Central Lancashire and in the main, duties will be carried out within the Preston Locality&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be willing to undergo an enhanced DBS check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;please contact Alex Stokes or Maxine Rigby on 01772 644659&lt;/p&gt;
